Servlet:

Use the `@Override` annotation also for interface methods, where it is optional.
It helps finding wrong method signatures (=unreached methods).

A servlet object is reused, serialized to disk, and so on. Hence modified
_fields_ are evil, and generally I would refrain from fields. For a fixed list, like here, it is possible, but I would do it using the life cycle methods:

    private List&lt;String&gt; bookTitles;

    @Override
    public void init() {
        // You might access the servlet config here.
        bookTitles = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
        Collections.addAll(bookTitles,
            &quot;Faith in Fakes: Travels in Hyperreality&quot;,
            &quot;Null-A&quot;,
            &quot;Wasp&quot;);
    }

    @Override
    ... doGet(...) ... {
        log(&quot;book_titles are passed: &quot; + bookTitles);
        ...
    }


JSP:

ISO-8859-1 is the standard HTTP encoding, Latin-1.
Nowadays and prescribed in HTML5 (you are using) that is interpreted
as the extended Windows Latin-1, Windows-1252 (even on Mac/Linux).
So comma like quotes and some other symbols may be displayed.

    ... charset=Windows-1252 ...  pageEncoding=&quot;Windows-1252&quot;

    ${requestScope.book_titles}

